                      no review signal                                          

[32mrepo object[0m

Top-level [2mrepo[0m describes the local checkout's repository as derived from the 
primary remote. [2mci.repo[0m describes the repository targeted by the PR/MR URL in 
[2mci.url[0m (for fork PRs, this is the upstream target). Existing [2mrepo_url[0m and 
[2mci.repo_url[0m fields remain available and carry the same URL as [2mrepo.url[0m / 
[2mci.repo.url[0m.

  Field    Type                           Description                           
 ──────── ────── ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── 
 [2murl[0m      string Repository web URL                                             
 [2mprovider[0m string [2m"github"[0m, [2m"gitlab"[0m, [2m"gitea"[0m, [2m"azure-devops"[0m, or [2m"unknown"[0m      
 [2mhost[0m     string Repository web host                                            
 [2mowner[0m    string Owner, organization, or namespace path                         
 [2mname[0m     string Repository name                                                
 [2mproject[0m  string Azure DevOps project name; absent for other providers          
 [2mremote[0m   string Local remote name used for top-level repo metadata; absent     
                 from [2mci.repo[0m                                                   

[32mmain_state values[0m

The single highest-priority state describing the branch's relation to the 
default branch; absent when none applies (a normal up-to-date branch). Each 
value is one Default-branch symbol — see Default branch for the symbol and the 
full meaning of each value ([2m"is_main"[0m, [2m"orphan"[0m, [2m"would_conflict"[0m, [2m"empty"[0m, 
[2m"same_commit"[0m, [2m"integrated"[0m, [2m"diverged"[0m, [2m"ahead"[0m, [2m"behind"[0m).

[32mintegration_reason values[0m

Set only when [2mmain_state == "integrated"[0m (the [2m⊂[0m symbol), recording which check 
matched. Checks run cheapest-first and the first match wins. JSON-only — every 
reason renders as the same [2m⊂[0m:

     Value                                  Meaning                             
 ────────────── ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── 
 [2m"ancestor"[0m     Branch HEAD is an ancestor of the default branch, which has     
                moved past it                                                   
 [2m"no-added-chan[0m The three-dot diff ([2mmain...branch[0m) is empty — no file changes   
 [2mges"[0m           beyond the merge-base                                           
 [2m"trees-match"[0m  Different history, but the branch's tree is identical to the    
                default branch's                                                
 [2m"merge-adds-no[0m The branch has changes, but merging them leaves the default     
 [2mthing"[0m         branch's tree unchanged (e.g. a squash merge where the target   
                advanced on other files)                                        
 [2m"patch-id-matc[0m The branch's squashed diff matches a single commit on the       
 [2mh"[0m             default branch (e.g. a GitHub/GitLab squash merge)              

[32mci.status and ci.review_state values[0m

The CI status section above is the single source for both fields: the table maps
 each colored value, and the notes below it cover [2m"draft"[0m and [2m"approved"[0m. 
[2mci.status[0m is one of [2m"passed"[0m, [2m"running"[0m, [2m"failed"[0m, [2m"conflicts"[0m, [2m"no-ci"[0m, 
[2m"error"[0m; [2mci.review_state[0m is one of [2m"changes_requested"[0m, [2m"pending"[0m, [2m"draft"[0m, 
[2m"approved"[0m, absent when the forge reports no review signal. The vocabulary 
matches Claude Code's statusline [2mpr.review_state[0m field.

Missing a field that would be generally useful? Open an issue at 
https://github.com/max-sixty/worktrunk.

